review_blob: On tap, at Beervana. The NZ beer festival. Not much on the nose initially, however develops into a creamy, vanilla, nutmeg plate as it warms. Very bright copper/orange hue. No evidence of starch haze, or astringent bitterness. Very tasty. Winner of the Saturday night beer of the session!

Draught, at Pomeroys in Christchurch. Pours very cloudy, but to style. Big citrus (orange) on the nose. Bitterness is in afterthought to the malt character. A pale ale vibe resonates from this very hoppy wheat beer. Very enjoyable

22oz Bottle, from Hashigo zake, Wellington, New Zealand. WTF Black IPA?? This beer is defiantly a great seasonal, mid to dark ale. Full copper tones. The nose suggests great piney Roguish characteristics, Flavor is an interesting mix of West Coast meets East Coast IPA, lots of grapefruit characteristics, which blend with the pine and caramel, resiny almost stone fruit of the malt. Would make a great fall beer and kept well enough to make it to New Zealand in one piece. .
